# Problem

If you enter an invalid custom report name formula / default report title, an error is displayed, but there isn't enough margin between it and the menu item above it. The problem will be especially noticeable for longer error messages that will be possible in the future, such as the example on dev with a draft backend PR.

<img width="1920" height="993" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a6651f34-c6a6-42bd-82cf-8620c616d911" />

On dev
<img width="1916" height="993" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2aaef87f-af36-4921-a925-6bf005865c31" />

You can set the error message to any text you like using this script, just paste it into the console on this page.


<details><summary>Snippet to set report title error</summary>

```js
// Set error for report title field - extracts policyID from URL
(() => {
    // Extract policyID from URL (format: /workspaces/:policyID/reports)
    const urlMatch = window.location.pathname.match(/\/workspaces\/([^\/]+)\/reports/);
    const policyID = urlMatch ? urlMatch[1] : null;

    if (!policyID) {
        console.error('Could not extract policyID from URL:', window.location.pathname);
        console.log('Please ensure you are on the workspace reports page');
        return;
    }

    // Use window.Onyx
    const Onyx = window.Onyx;

    if (!Onyx) {
        console.error('Onyx not found on window object');
        return;
    }

    // Generate microsecond timestamp for error key
    const timestamp = Date.now() * 1000;

    // Set the error (hardcoded ONYXKEYS.COLLECTION.POLICY = 'policy_')
    Onyx.merge(`policy_${policyID}`, {
        errorFields: {
            fieldList: {
                'text_title': {
                    defaultValue: {
                        [timestamp]: 'Test super long error message for report title that really is way to long and expands vertically causing overlap errors with the menu item. It will need to be even longer to cause the error so here is some more text to make it longer.'
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    });

    console.log(`✅ Error set for report title field on policy ${policyID}`);
})();
```

</details> 


# Solution
Fix the display of the error message as explained by @shawnborton [here (internal)](https://github.com/Expensify/Web-Expensify/pull/48923#issuecomment-3400815982)

> keep the error message contained within the row above, so that when you hover, it's like you are giving the entire wrapper (row above plus message) a background hover style.
